"{\"uid\": \"greekreporter.com-2025-10-14-lycurgus-sparta-founder-olympic-games\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"One very prominent figure from early Greek history is Lycurgus ofSparta.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 72, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 37, \"end\": 42, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9998437924906476, \"rank\": 0.00015390681806301329, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One very prominent figure\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 25}, {\"ngram\": \"Lycurgus\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 62}, {\"ngram\": \"ofSparta\", \"from\": 63, \"to\": 71}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was the famous lawmaker of the city-state.\", \"from\": 73, \"to\": 118, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the famous lawmaker\", \"from\": 80, \"to\": 99}, {\"ngram\": \"the city-state\", \"from\": 103, \"to\": 117}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, another accomplishment that Greek tradition attributes to him is the founding ofGreece's most famous sporting festival.\", \"from\": 119, \"to\": 247, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 156, \"end\": 161, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9998437924906476, \"rank\": 0.00015390681806301329, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"another accomplishment\", \"from\": 128, \"to\": 150}, {\"ngram\": \"the founding ofGreece's most famous sporting festival\", \"from\": 193, \"to\": 246}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What does the evidence really reveal about this subject?\", \"from\": 248, \"to\": 304, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the evidence\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 270}, {\"ngram\": \"this subject\", \"from\": 291, \"to\": 303}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Did Lycurgus of Sparta reallyfound the Olympic Games?\", \"from\": 305, \"to\": 358, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 309, \"end\": 317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"score\": 0.9273411128360276, \"rank\": 0.07818576381811959, \"text\": \"Lycurgus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\"}, {\"begin\": 321, \"end\": 327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sparta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.048025749304715e-39, \"text\": \"Sparta\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sparta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sparta\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 340, \"to\": 357}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us first examine what the tradition in question actually claims.\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 428, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 364, \"to\": 366}, {\"ngram\": \"the tradition\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 399}, {\"ngram\": \"question\", \"from\": 403, \"to\": 411}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The surviving source for this tradition isPlutarch, a Greek philosopher of the first century CE.\", \"from\": 429, \"to\": 525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 483, \"end\": 488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9998437924906476, \"rank\": 0.00015390681806301329, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The surviving source\", \"from\": 429, \"to\": 449}, {\"ngram\": \"this tradition isPlutarch\", \"from\": 454, \"to\": 479}, {\"ngram\": \"the first century CE\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 524}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to Plutarch, Aristotle believed that Lycurgus was associated with the first Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 526, \"to\": 626, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 549, \"end\": 558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.923844753693786e-20, \"text\": \"Aristotle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle\"}, {\"begin\": 573, \"end\": 581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"score\": 0.9273411128360276, \"rank\": 0.07818576381811959, \"text\": \"Lycurgus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Plutarch\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 547}, {\"ngram\": \"the first Olympic Games\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 625}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the words of Plutarch: \\\"Some say that he flourished at the same time with Iphitus, and in concert with him established the Olympic truce.\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 705, \"end\": 712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iphitos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.0996556595349824e-20, \"text\": \"Iphitus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iphitos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iphitos\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the words\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 639}, {\"ngram\": \"Plutarch\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 651}, {\"ngram\": \"the same time\", \"from\": 685, \"to\": 698}, {\"ngram\": \"concert\", \"from\": 720, \"to\": 727}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic truce\", \"from\": 749, \"to\": 766}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among these is Aristotle the philosopher, and he alleges as proof the discus at Olympia on which an inscription preserves the name of Lycurgus.\\\"\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 913, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 784, \"end\": 793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.923844753693786e-20, \"text\": \"Aristotle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle\"}, {\"begin\": 849, \"end\": 856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Opel_Olympia\", \"score\": 0.6727135073609423, \"rank\": 0.4865169036415976, \"text\": \"Olympia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Opel_Olympia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Opel_Olympia\"}, {\"begin\": 903, \"end\": 911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"score\": 0.9273411128360276, \"rank\": 0.07818576381811959, \"text\": \"Lycurgus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the philosopher\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 809}, {\"ngram\": \"proof\", \"from\": 829, \"to\": 834}, {\"ngram\": \"the discus\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 845}, {\"ngram\": \"an inscription\", \"from\": 866, \"to\": 880}, {\"ngram\": \"the name\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 899}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Iphitus is a figure that appears in other records of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 915, \"to\": 981, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 915, \"end\": 922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iphitos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.0996556595349824e-20, \"text\": \"Iphitus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iphitos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iphitos\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a figure\", \"from\": 926, \"to\": 934}, {\"ngram\": \"other records\", \"from\": 951, \"to\": 964}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 980}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was the king of Elis and was supposedly the founder of the festival.\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 1053, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1001, \"end\": 1005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Elis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6156985291089918e-17, \"text\": \"Elis\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Elis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Elis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the king\", \"from\": 989, \"to\": 997}, {\"ngram\": \"the founder\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1036}, {\"ngram\": \"the festival\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1052}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thus, in this passage, Plutarch is saying that Aristotle (among others) believed that Lycurgus worked alongside Iphitus to establish the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1205, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1101, \"end\": 1110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.923844753693786e-20, \"text\": \"Aristotle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle\"}, {\"begin\": 1140, \"end\": 1148, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"score\": 0.9273411128360276, \"rank\": 0.07818576381811959, \"text\": \"Lycurgus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\"}, {\"begin\": 1166, \"end\": 1173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iphitos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.0996556595349824e-20, \"text\": \"Iphitus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iphitos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iphitos\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this passage\", \"from\": 1063, \"to\": 1075}, {\"ngram\": \"Plutarch\", \"from\": 1077, \"to\": 1085}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1124}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1187, \"to\": 1204}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Something very useful about this tradition is that we actually know exactly what the supposed evidence for it is.\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1320, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Something\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1216}, {\"ngram\": \"this tradition\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1249}, {\"ngram\": \"exactly what\", \"from\": 1275, \"to\": 1287}, {\"ngram\": \"the supposed evidence\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1309}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As we can see from the quotation from Plutarch, the alleged proof presented by Aristotle was the existence of a discus at Olympia which had the name \\\"Lycurgus\\\" inscribed on it.\", \"from\": 1321, \"to\": 1497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1359, \"end\": 1367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plutarch\", \"score\": 0.9999999994306563, \"rank\": 5.693566110231706e-10, \"text\": \"Plutarch\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plutarch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plutarch\"}, {\"begin\": 1400, \"end\": 1409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.923844753693786e-20, \"text\": \"Aristotle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle\"}, {\"begin\": 1443, \"end\": 1450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Opel_Olympia\", \"score\": 0.6727135073609423, \"rank\": 0.4865169036415976, \"text\": \"Olympia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Opel_Olympia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Opel_Olympia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the quotation\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1353}, {\"ngram\": \"the alleged proof\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1386}, {\"ngram\": \"the existence\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1427}, {\"ngram\": \"a discus\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1439}, {\"ngram\": \"the name\", \"from\": 1461, \"to\": 1469}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Lycurgus\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1479}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By knowing the proof, we are in a reasonable position to assess whether or not this tradition is actually convincing.\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1616, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the proof\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1519}, {\"ngram\": \"a reasonable position\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1552}, {\"ngram\": \"this tradition\", \"from\": 1578, \"to\": 1592}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hence, what can we say regarding this ancient claim?\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1669, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this ancient claim\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1668}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Firstly, there are some scholars who believe that the inscription in question is not genuine but was a forgery from the fourth century BCE.\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1810, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1806, \"end\": 1809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Common_Era\", \"score\": 0.9999997544892113, \"rank\": 2.455108831700757e-07, \"text\": \"BCE\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Common_Era\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Common_Era\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some scholars\", \"from\": 1690, \"to\": 1703}, {\"ngram\": \"the inscription\", \"from\": 1721, \"to\": 1736}, {\"ngram\": \"question\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1748}, {\"ngram\": \"a forgery\", \"from\": 1772, \"to\": 1781}, {\"ngram\": \"the fourth century\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1805}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of course, such a conclusion can only be speculation since we have no additional information about the discus.\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1921, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such a conclusion\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1839}, {\"ngram\": \"speculation\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 1863}, {\"ngram\": \"no additional information\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 1903}, {\"ngram\": \"the discus\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 1920}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A more significant issue is the simple fact that Plutarch's description of Aristotle's claim does not present any reason to believe that the Lycurgus mentioned on the inscription was the famous lawgiver of Sparta.\", \"from\": 1923, \"to\": 2136, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1972, \"end\": 1980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plutarch\", \"score\": 0.9999999994306563, \"rank\": 5.693566110231706e-10, \"text\": \"Plutarch\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plutarch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plutarch\"}, {\"begin\": 1998, \"end\": 2007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.923844753693786e-20, \"text\": \"Aristotle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle\"}, {\"begin\": 2064, \"end\": 2072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"score\": 0.9273411128360276, \"rank\": 0.07818576381811959, \"text\": \"Lycurgus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\"}, {\"begin\": 2129, \"end\": 2135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sparta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.048025749304715e-39, \"text\": \"Sparta\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sparta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sparta\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A more significant issue\", \"from\": 1923, \"to\": 1947}, {\"ngram\": \"the simple fact\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 1966}, {\"ngram\": \"any reason\", \"from\": 2033, \"to\": 2043}, {\"ngram\": \"the inscription\", \"from\": 2086, \"to\": 2101}, {\"ngram\": \"the famous lawgiver\", \"from\": 2106, \"to\": 2125}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Based on Plutarch's words, it seems that the discus simply had the name \\\"Lycurgus\\\" on it.\", \"from\": 2138, \"to\": 2227, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2147, \"end\": 2155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plutarch\", \"score\": 0.9999999994306563, \"rank\": 5.693566110231706e-10, \"text\": \"Plutarch\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plutarch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plutarch\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the discus\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2189}, {\"ngram\": \"the name\", \"from\": 2201, \"to\": 2209}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Lycurgus\", \"from\": 2210, \"to\": 2219}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is no suggestion that the inscription explained who, exactly, this Lycurgus was.\", \"from\": 2228, \"to\": 2314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2301, \"end\": 2309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"score\": 0.9273411128360276, \"rank\": 0.07818576381811959, \"text\": \"Lycurgus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no suggestion\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2250}, {\"ngram\": \"the inscription\", \"from\": 2256, \"to\": 2271}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is a problem because this was not an uncommon name.\", \"from\": 2315, \"to\": 2371, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a problem\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2332}, {\"ngram\": \"an uncommon name\", \"from\": 2354, \"to\": 2370}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, we can findat least eight figures with the name Lycurgusin the legends ofGreek mythology.\", \"from\": 2372, \"to\": 2470, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 2375, \"to\": 2379}, {\"ngram\": \"least eight figures\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2414}, {\"ngram\": \"the name\", \"from\": 2420, \"to\": 2428}, {\"ngram\": \"Lycurgusin\", \"from\": 2429, \"to\": 2439}, {\"ngram\": \"the legends\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2451}, {\"ngram\": \"mythology\", \"from\": 2460, \"to\": 2469}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Therefore, even if this was a genuine inscription from the first Olympic Games, it would not prove that Lycurgus of Sparta was involved.\", \"from\": 2472, \"to\": 2608, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2576, \"end\": 2584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"score\": 0.9273411128360276, \"rank\": 0.07818576381811959, \"text\": \"Lycurgus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\"}, {\"begin\": 2588, \"end\": 2594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sparta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.048025749304715e-39, \"text\": \"Sparta\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sparta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sparta\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a genuine inscription\", \"from\": 2500, \"to\": 2521}, {\"ngram\": \"the first Olympic Games\", \"from\": 2527, \"to\": 2550}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is especially so when we consider the chronological issues involved in the tradition.\", \"from\": 2609, \"to\": 2699, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the chronological issues\", \"from\": 2648, \"to\": 2672}, {\"ngram\": \"the tradition\", \"from\": 2685, \"to\": 2698}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic Games were founded in 776 BCE according toancient Greekrecords.\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2776, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympic Games\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2718}, {\"ngram\": \"776 BCE\", \"from\": 2735, \"to\": 2742}, {\"ngram\": \"toancient Greekrecords\", \"from\": 2753, \"to\": 2775}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If Lycurgus of Sparta was involved in founding the Olympics, then obviously, he must have lived in the first half of the eighth century BCE.\", \"from\": 2777, \"to\": 2917, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2780, \"end\": 2788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"score\": 0.9273411128360276, \"rank\": 0.07818576381811959, \"text\": \"Lycurgus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\"}, {\"begin\": 2792, \"end\": 2798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sparta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.048025749304715e-39, \"text\": \"Sparta\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sparta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sparta\"}, {\"begin\": 2913, \"end\": 2916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Common_Era\", \"score\": 0.9999997544892113, \"rank\": 2.455108831700757e-07, \"text\": \"BCE\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Common_Era\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Common_Era\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2824, \"to\": 2836}, {\"ngram\": \"the first half\", \"from\": 2876, \"to\": 2890}, {\"ngram\": \"the eighth century\", \"from\": 2894, \"to\": 2912}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, does the evidence really support this conclusion?\", \"from\": 2918, \"to\": 2976, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the evidence\", \"from\": 2932, \"to\": 2944}, {\"ngram\": \"this conclusion\", \"from\": 2960, \"to\": 2975}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In reality, the evidence strongly supports the conclusion that Lycurgus lived at around the middle of the seventh century BCE.\", \"from\": 2978, \"to\": 3104, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3041, \"end\": 3049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"score\": 0.9273411128360276, \"rank\": 0.07818576381811959, \"text\": \"Lycurgus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lycurgus_of_Athens\"}, {\"begin\": 3100, \"end\": 3103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Common_Era\", \"score\": 0.9999997544892113, \"rank\": 2.455108831700757e-07, \"text\": \"BCE\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Common_Era\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Common_Era\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"reality\", \"from\": 2981, \"to\": 2988}, {\"ngram\": \"the evidence\", \"from\": 2990, \"to\": 3002}, {\"ngram\": \"